/__init__.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py","metadata":{"count":28,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z","time":{"start":1775900324236,"end":1775900324258}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900324273,"sessionID":"ses_28417dd66ffeB506LTdirue3Y0","part":{"id":"prt_d7be87170001iiGMBCU3zToMUs","messageID":"msg_d7be835b70015YdGf633I3scRz","sessionID":"ses_28417dd66ffeB506LTdirue3Y0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7a36158d50db449194e932e3dfd82c91","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec.md — AR-038 Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n2: \n3: ## AR-038 — Go Unit Tests (pkg/workloadmanager)\n4: \n5: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n6: **Language:** Go  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Base specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## OpenSpec Format\n13: \n14: Each requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## REQ-001: Error Types and HTTP Response Handling\n19: \n20: ### Description\n21: The workloadmanager package defines custom error types and a unified HTTP error response handler that maps errors to appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON response bodies.\n22: \n23: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: ValidationError returns 400 BadRequest\n26: - **GIVEN** a ValidationError with Field=\"name\" and Reason=\"required\"\n27: - **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n28: - **THEN** HTTP status is 400\n29: - **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\"}`\n30: - **AND** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: NotFoundError returns 404 NotFound\n33: - **GIVEN** a NotFoundError with Resource=\"agentruntime\" and Name=\"test-runtime\"\n34: - **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n35: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404\n36: - **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\"}`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: InternalError returns 500 InternalServerError\n39: - **GIVEN** an InternalError wrapping a database connection error\n40: - **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n41: - **THEN** HTTP status is 500\n42: - **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", \"message\": \"Unexpected server error\"}`\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: ServiceUnavailableError returns 503 ServiceUnavailable\n45: - **GIVEN** a ServiceUnavailableError with Dependency=\"kubernetes-api\"\n46: - **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n47: - **THEN** HTTP status is 503\n48: - **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"}`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Unknown error type defaults to 500 InternalServerError\n51: - **GIVEN** a generic Go error not matching any custom error type\n52: - **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n53: - **THEN** HTTP status is 500\n54: - **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"}`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Error type implements Error() interface correctly\n57: - **GIVEN** each custom error type (ValidationError, NotFoundError, InternalError, ServiceUnavailableError, ConflictError)\n58: - **WHEN** Error() method is called\n59: - **THEN** returns formatted string matching expected pattern\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## REQ-002: MemoryStore CRUD Operations\n64: \n65: ### Description\n66: MemoryStore provides thread-safe in-memory storage for SandboxInfo records with full CRUD operations, expiration tracking, and batch querying capabilities.\n67: \n68: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds new sandbox to store\n71: - **GIVEN** a new MemoryStore instance\n72: - **AND** a SandboxInfo with SessionID=\"session-123\", SandboxID=\"sandbox-123\", ExpiresAt set to 8 hours from now\n73: - **WHEN** StoreSandbox is called\n74: - **THEN** no error is returned\n75: - **AND** store.Size() equals 1\n76: - **AND** expirationIndex contains the sandbox's expiration time\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves existing sandbox\n79: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with a stored sandbox having SessionID=\"session-123\"\n80: - **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with \"session-123\"\n81: - **THEN** no error is returned\n82: - **AND** returned SandboxInfo matches the stored sandbox\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n85: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with no sandbox for \"non-existent\"\n86: - **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with \"non-existent\"\n87: - **THEN** NotFoundError is returned\n88: - **AND** error type is NotFoundError\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies existing sandbox\n91: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with a sandbox having Status=\"running\"\n92: - **WHEN** UpdateSandbox is called with Status=\"terminating\" and LastActivity updated\n93: - **THEN** no error is returned\n94: - **AND** subsequent GetSandboxBySessionID returns updated Status and LastActivity\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n97: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with no sandbox\n98: - **WHEN** UpdateSandbox is called with SessionID=\"non-existent\"\n99: - **THEN** NotFoundError is returned\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n102: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one sandbox\n103: - **WHEN** DeleteSandboxBySessionID is called\n104: - **THEN** no error is returned\n105: - **AND** store.Size() equals 0\n106: - **AND** GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID succeeds for non-existent sandbox\n109: - **GIVEN** an empty MemoryStore\n110: - **WHEN** DeleteSandboxBySessionID is called with any sessionID\n111: - **THEN** no error is returned (idempotent deletion)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: ListSandboxes returns all stored sandboxes\n114: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 3 sandboxes stored\n115: - **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called\n116: - **THEN** no error is returned\n117: - **AND** returned list contains exactly 3 SandboxInfo records\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes filters by expiration time\n120: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one expired sandbox (ExpiresAt before now) and one active sandbox\n121: - **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with now as threshold\n122: - **THEN** only expired sandbox is returned\n123: - **AND** active sandbox is excluded\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit parameter\n126: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 20 expired sandboxes\n127: - **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with limit=5\n128: - **THEN** exactly 5 sandboxes are returned\n129: - **AND** results are sorted by ExpiresAt (oldest first)\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes filters by LastActivity\n132: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one inactive sandbox (LastActivity 30 minutes ago), one active sandbox, and one with no LastActivity set\n133: - **WHEN** ListInactiveSandboxes is called with threshold 15 minutes ago\n134: - **THEN** only inactive sandbox is returned\n135: - **AND** active sandbox and no-activity sandbox are excluded\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit parameter\n138: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 20 inactive sandboxes\n139: - **WHEN** ListInactiveSandboxes is called with limit=5\n140: - **THEN** exactly 5 sandboxes are returned\n141: - **AND** results are sorted by LastActivity (oldest first)\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Clear removes all sandboxes\n144: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with sandboxes stored\n145: - **WHEN** Clear is called\n146: - **THEN** store.Size() equals 0\n147: - **AND** both sandboxes map and expirationIndex are empty\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Concurrent access is thread-safe\n150: - **GIVEN** a MemoryStore\n151: - **WHEN** 100 concurrent StoreSandbox, 100 concurrent GetSandboxBySessionID, and 50 concurrent DeleteSandboxBySessionID operations run\n152: - **THEN** no race condition occurs\n153: - **AND** all operations complete without panic or deadlock\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## REQ-003: SandboxLifecycleManager\n158: \n159: ### Description\n160: SandboxLifecycleManager orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, expiration checking, and status updates with Kubernetes API integration.\n161: \n162: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig returns expected defaults\n165: - **GIVEN** DefaultLifecycleConfig function\n166: - **WHEN** called\n167: - **THEN** DefaultTTL equals 8 hours\n168: - **AND** DefaultIdleTimeout equals 15 minutes\n169: - **AND** DefaultMaxDuration equals 8 hours\n170: - **AND** GCInterval equals 2 minutes\n171: - **AND** DeletionTimeout equals 30 seconds\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: NewSandboxLifecycleManager initializes correctly\n174: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient, MemoryStore, LifecycleConfig, and Logger\n175: - **WHEN** NewSandboxLifecycleManager is called\n176: - **THEN** manager.k8sClient equals provided K8sClient\n177: - **AND** manager.store equals provided Store\n178: - **AND** manager.config equals provided config\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox removes sandbox from store and Kubernetes\n181: - **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager with sandbox stored in MemoryStore\n182: - **AND** sandbox having SandboxNamespace=\"default\", SandboxName=\"sandbox-123\"\n183: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with sessionID\n184: - **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n185: - **AND** Kubernetes Delete call is made with correct namespace/name\n186: - **AND** no error is returned\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox returns NotFoundError for missing session\n189: - **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager with empty store\n190: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with \"non-existent\"\n191: - **THEN** NotFoundError with Resource=\"session\" is returned\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles SandboxClaim deletion when Kind is SandboxClaim\n194: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n195: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called\n196: - **THEN** both Sandbox and SandboxClaim resources are deleted from Kubernetes\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: IsExpired correctly detects expired sandbox\n199: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with ExpiresAt 1 hour ago\n200: - **WHEN** IsExpired is called\n201: - **THEN** returns true\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: IsExpired returns false for active sandbox\n204: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with ExpiresAt 8 hours from now\n205: - **WHEN** IsExpired is called\n206: - **THEN** returns false\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: IsIdleExpired returns false for sandbox with no activity\n209: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with LastActivity zero value\n210: - **WHEN** IsIdleExpired is called with any idleTimeout\n211: - **THEN** returns false\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: IsIdleExpired detects idle timeout breach\n214: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with LastActivity 30 minutes ago\n215: - **AND** idleTimeout of 15 minutes\n216: - **WHEN** IsIdleExpired is called\n217: - **THEN** returns true\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: ForceDeleteSandbox removes sandbox with gracePeriodSeconds=0\n220: - **GIVEN** a stored sandbox\n221: - **WHEN** ForceDeleteSandbox is called\n222: - **THEN** sandbox is deleted from Kubernetes with GracePeriodSeconds=0\n223: - **AND** sandbox is removed from store\n224: - **AND** no error is returned\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: ForceDeleteSandbox succeeds even for non-existent session\n227: - **GIVEN** empty store\n228: - **WHEN** ForceDeleteSandbox is called with any sessionID\n229: - **THEN** no error is returned (returns nil for NotFound)\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: GetSandbox retrieves sandbox from store\n232: - **GIVEN** a store with sandbox having SessionID=\"session-123\"\n233: - **WHEN** GetSandbox is called\n234: - **THEN** SandboxInfo is returned correctly\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: UpdateSandboxStatus modifies sandbox status\n237: - **GIVEN** a store with sandbox having Status=\"running\"\n238: - **WHEN** UpdateSandboxStatus is called with newStatus=\"terminating\"\n239: - **THEN** sandbox Status is updated\n240: - **AND** no error is returned\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns nil for NotFound Kubernetes error\n243: - **GIVEN** an apierrors.IsNotFound error\n244: - **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n245: - **THEN** nil is returned\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns ConflictError for Kubernetes conflict\n248: - **GIVEN** an apierrors.IsConflict error\n249: - **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n250: - **THEN** ConflictError is returned\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns InternalError for other errors\n253: - **GIVEN** a generic error\n254: - **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n255: - **THEN** InternalError wrapping the original error is returned\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns MaxDurationReached for expired sandbox\n258: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with ExpiresAt before now\n259: - **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n260: - **THEN** DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached is returned\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns IdleTimeout for idle sandbox\n263: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with ExpiresAt after now but LastActivity idle\n264: - **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n265: - **THEN** DeletionReasonIdleTimeout is returned\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns UserRequest for active sandbox\n268: - **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n269: - **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n270: - **THEN** DeletionReasonUserRequest is returned\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## REQ-004: GarbageCollector\n275: \n276: ### Description\n277: GarbageCollector runs periodic cleanup of expired and inactive sandboxes with configurable intervals, batch limits, and timeout controls.\n278: \n279: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector initializes with defaults\n282: - **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager and interval=0, onceTimeout=0\n283: - **WHEN** NewGarbageCollector is called\n284: - **THEN** interval defaults to GarbageCollectorInterval (2 minutes)\n285: - **AND** onceTimeout defaults to 2 minutes\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector uses provided values\n288: - **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager and custom interval=100ms, onceTimeout=1s\n289: - **WHEN** NewGarbageCollector is called\n290: - **THEN** gc.interval equals 100ms\n291: - **AND** gc.onceTimeout equals 1s\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Start and Stop work correctly\n294: - **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector\n295: - **WHEN** Start is called then Stop is called after 50ms\n296: - **THEN** garbage collector stops cleanly\n297: - **AND** runLoop goroutine exits\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandboxes\n300: - **GIVEN** a store with one expired sandbox and one active sandbox\n301: - **WHEN** runOnce is called\n302: - **THEN** expired sandbox is deleted\n303: - **AND** active sandbox remains in store\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandboxes\n306: - **GIVEN** a store with one inactive sandbox (LastActivity old) and one active sandbox\n307: - **WHEN** runOnce is called\n308: - **THEN** inactive sandbox is deleted\n309: - **AND** active sandbox remains in store\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: runOnce respects GCBatchSize limit\n312: - **GIVEN** a store with 20 expired sandboxes\n313: - **WHEN** runOnce is called\n314: - **THEN** at most GCBatchSize (16) sandboxes are deleted per run\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: runOnce continues on individual deletion errors\n317: - **GIVEN** a store with 3 expired sandboxes\n318: - **WHEN** runOnce is called and some deletions fail\n319: - **THEN** processing continues for remaining sandboxes\n320: - **AND** error is logged but not returned\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: GetStats returns current configuration\n323: - **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector with custom settings\n324: - **WHEN** GetStats is called\n325: - **THEN** GarbageCollectorStats contains current Interval, OnceTimeout, and IdleTimeout\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout updates idle timeout value\n328: - **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector\n329: - **WHEN** SetIdleTimeout is called with new value\n330: - **THEN** subsequent GetStats returns updated IdleTimeout\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Concurrent runOnce calls are safe\n333: - **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector with 10 expired sandboxes\n334: - **WHEN** 3 concurrent runOnce calls execute\n335: - **THEN** no race condition occurs\n336: - **AND** store size is at or below 10 minus deletions\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## REQ-005: HTTPServer\n341: \n342: ### Description\n343: HTTPServer manages the HTTP server lifecycle with chi router, handler registration, graceful shutdown, and timeout configuration.\n344: \n345: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: NewHTTPServer initializes with default config\n348: - **GIVEN** a Config and Logger\n349: - **WHEN** NewHTTPServer is called\n350: - **THEN** server.router is chi.Router instance\n351: - **AND** server.handlers is empty map\n352: - **AND** server.stopCh is initialized\n353: - **AND** server.store is MemoryStore instance\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: RegisterHandler stores and registers handler\n356: - **GIVEN** an HTTPServer and a Handler implementation\n357: - **WHEN** RegisterHandler is called with name=\"test\"\n358: - **THEN** handler is stored in handlers map\n359: - **AND** handler's Register method is called with router\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Start returns error channel\n362: - **GIVEN** an HTTPServer with config.Addr=\":0\"\n363: - **WHEN** Start is called\n364: - **THEN** error channel is returned\n365: - **AND** server begins listening\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Stop closes stopCh and shuts down server\n368: - **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer\n369: - **WHEN** Stop is called with context\n370: - **THEN** stopCh is closed\n371: - **AND** server.Shutdown is called with timeout\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Router handles registered routes\n374: - **GIVEN** an HTTPServer with a route registered at \"/test\"\n375: - **WHEN** HTTP request is made to \"/test\"\n376: - **THEN** route handler is invoked\n377: - **AND** correct HTTP status is returned\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: NewHTTPServerWithClients initializes with K8sClient and Store\n380: - **GIVEN** Config, Logger, K8sClient, and custom Store\n381: - **WHEN** NewHTTPServerWithClients is called\n382: - **THEN** lifecycleManager is initialized\n383: - **AND** garbageCollector is initialized\n384: - **AND** provided store is used\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ## REQ-006: K8sClient\n389: \n390: ### Description\n391: K8sClient wraps Kubernetes dynamic client, core client, and informer factory for managing Kubernetes resources and watching Pod state.\n392: \n393: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n394: \n395: #### Scenario: NewK8sClient creates all components\n396: - **GIVEN** a rest.Config\n397: - **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called\n398: - **THEN** dynamicClient is created\n399: - **AND** coreClient is created\n400: - **AND** informerFactory is created\n401: - **AND** podLister is initialized\n402: - **AND** scheme includes corev1\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: StartInformers starts factory\n405: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient with informerFactory\n406: - **WHEN** StartInformers is called with context\n407: - **THEN** informerFactory.Start is invoked\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync returns true when synced\n410: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient with started informers\n411: - **WHEN** WaitForCacheSync is called\n412: - **THEN** returns true if all informers synced\n413: - **AND** returns false if any informer not synced\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: PodLister retrieves pods after sync\n416: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient with a Pod in the fake client\n417: - **WHEN** informers are started and synced\n418: - **THEN** PodLister can retrieve the Pod by name/namespace\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: DynamicClient returns dynamic interface\n421: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n422: - **WHEN** DynamicClient() is called\n423: - **THEN** returns the dynamic.Interface\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: CoreClient returns kubernetes interface\n426: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n427: - **WHEN** CoreClient() is called\n428: - **THEN** returns kubernetes.Interface\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: ClientCache GetOrCreateClient caches clients\n431: - **GIVEN** a ClientCache with rest.Config\n432: - **WHEN** GetOrCreateClient is called twice with same token+namespace\n433: - **THEN** same client instance is returned both times\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: ClientCache creates different clients for different keys\n436: - **GIVEN** a ClientCache\n437: - **WHEN** GetOrCreateClient is called with different token+namespace combinations\n438: - **THEN** different client instances are returned\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## REQ-007: Config and Defaults\n443: \n444: ### Description\n445: Config struct holds HTTP server configuration with default values for timeouts, address, and health endpoints.\n446: \n447: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n448: \n449: #### Scenario: DefaultConfig returns sensible defaults\n450: - **GIVEN** DefaultConfig function\n451: - **WHEN** called\n452: - **THEN** Addr is \":8080\"\n453: - **AND** ReadTimeout is 15 seconds\n454: - **AND** WriteTimeout is 15 seconds\n455: - **AND** IdleTimeout is 60 seconds\n456: - **AND** ShutdownTimeout is 30 seconds\n457: - **AND** EnableHealthz is true\n458: - **AND** EnableReadyz is true\n459: \n460: #### Scenario: Config fields are accessible\n461: - **GIVEN** a custom Config instance\n462: - **WHEN** fields are read or written\n463: - **THEN** all timeout values and flags are accessible\n464: \n465: ---\n466: \n467: ## REQ-008: Constants and GVR Definitions\n468: \n469: ### Description\n470: defaults.go defines time constants, label keys, annotation keys, and GroupVersionResource definitions for Sandbox and SandboxClaim.\n471: \n472: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n473: \n474: #### Scenario: Time constants have expected values\n475: - **GIVEN** constants in defaults.go\n476: - **WHEN** values are checked\n477: - **THEN** DefaultSandboxTTL equals 8 hours\n478: - **AND** DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout equals 15 minutes\n479: - **AND** DefaultMaxSessionDuration equals 8 hours\n480: - **AND** SandboxCreationTimeout equals 2 minutes\n481: - **AND** SandboxDeleteTimeout equals 30 seconds\n482: - **AND** InformerSyncTimeout equals 1 minute\n483: - **AND** GarbageCollectorInterval equals 2 minutes\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: SandboxGVR has correct GroupVersionResource\n486: - **GIVEN** SandboxGVR variable\n487: - **WHEN** inspected\n488: - **THEN** Group is \"agents.x-k8s.io\"\n489: - **AND** Version is \"v1alpha1\"\n490: - **AND** Resource is \"sandboxes\"\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: SandboxClaimGVR has correct GroupVersionResource\n493: - **GIVEN** SandboxClaimGVR variable\n494: - **WHEN** inspected\n495: - **THEN** Group is \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"\n496: - **AND** Version is \"v1alpha1\"\n497: - **AND** Resource is \"sandboxclaims\"\n498: \n499: #### Scenario: Label keys match expected format\n500: - **GIVEN** label key constants\n501: - **WHEN** inspected\n502: - **THEN** LabelKeySessionID equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n503: - **AND** LabelKeyWorkloadName equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n504: - **AND** LabelKeySandboxName equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## REQ-009: Router\n509: \n510: ### Description\n511: Router wraps chi.Router providing simplified routing interface with handler registration support.\n512: \n513: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n514: \n515: #### Scenario: NewRouter creates chi.Router instance\n516: - **GIVEN** NewRouter function\n517: - **WHEN** called\n518: - **THEN** Router wraps a chi.Router\n519: \n520: #### Scenario: RegisterHandlers calls Register on each handler\n521: - **GIVEN** a Router and multiple Handler implementations\n522: - **WHEN** RegisterHandlers is called\n523: - **THEN** each handler's Register method is called\n524: \n525: ---\n526: \n527: ## REQ-010: Informers\n528: \n529: ### Description\n530: Informers wraps SharedInformerFactory for starting informers and waiting for cache sync.\n531: \n532: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n533: \n534: #### Scenario: NewInformers creates from K8sClient\n535: - **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n536: - **WHEN** NewInformers is called\n537: - **THEN** factory equals K8sClient's informerFactory\n538: \n539: #### Scenario: Start begins informer factory\n540: - **GIVEN** an Informers instance\n541: - **WHEN** Start is called with context\n542: - **THEN** factory.Start is invoked\n543: \n544: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync returns sync status\n545: - **GIVEN** an Informers instance with started factory\n546: - **WHEN** WaitForCacheSync is called\n547: - **THEN** returns true if all synced\n548: - **AND** returns false if any not synced\n549: \n550: ---\n551: \n552: ## REQ-011: HealthHandler\n553: \n554: ### Description\n555: HealthHandler provides /healthz and /readyz endpoints for Kubernetes probes with optional HealthChecker.\n556: \n557: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n558: \n559: #### Scenario: healthz always returns 200 OK\n560: - **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with any HealthChecker (even nil)\n561: - **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n562: - **THEN** status is 200\n563: - **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n564: \n565: #### Scenario: readyz returns 200 when checker IsReady is true\n566: - **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with HealthChecker.IsReady returning true\n567: - **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n568: - **THEN** status is 200\n569: - **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n570: \n571: #### Scenario: readyz returns 503 when checker IsReady is false\n572: - **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with HealthChecker.IsReady returning false\n573: - **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n574: - **THEN** status is 503\n575: - **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n576: \n577: #### Scenario: readyz returns 503 when checker is nil\n578: - **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with nil HealthChecker\n579: - **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n580: - **THEN** status is 503\n581: - **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: Both endpoints return JSON Content-Type\n584: - **GIVEN** a HealthHandler\n585: - **WHEN** either /healthz or /readyz is requested\n586: - **THEN** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ## REQ-012: DeletionHandler\n591: \n592: ### Description\n593: DeletionHandler handles DELETE requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sessions via SandboxLifecycleManager.\n594: \n595: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n596: \n597: #### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime sandbox succeeds\n598: - **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with valid sessionID in URL param\n599: - **AND** sandbox exists in store\n600: - **WHEN** DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId} is requested\n601: - **THEN** status is 200\n602: - **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"deleted\"}`\n603: \n604: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox succeeds\n605: - **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with valid sessionID\n606: - **WHEN** DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId} is requested\n607: - **THEN** status is 200\n608: - **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"deleted\"}`\n609: \n610: #### Scenario: Delete with empty sessionID returns ValidationError\n611: - **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler\n612: - **WHEN** DELETE request has empty sessionId\n613: - **THEN** status is 400\n614: - **AND** ValidationError for Field=\"sessionId\" is returned\n615: \n616: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent session returns 404\n617: - **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with no sandbox in store\n618: - **WHEN** DELETE request is made with valid sessionID\n619: - **THEN** status is 404\n620: - **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n621: \n622: ---\n623: \n624: ## REQ-013: CORS Middleware\n625: \n626: ### Description\n627: CORSMiddleware adds CORS headers to responses based on allowed origins configuration.\n628: \n629: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n630: \n631: #### Scenario: Allowed origin receives CORS headers\n632: - **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins containing \"http://example.com\"\n633: - **AND** request with Origin=\"http://example.com\"\n634: - **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n635: - **THEN** Access-Control-Allow-Origin is \"http://example.com\"\n636: - **AND** Access-Control-Allow-Methods and Headers are set\n637: - **AND** Allow-Credentials is set if configured\n638: \n639: #### Scenario: Disallowed origin receives no CORS headers\n640: - **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins containing only \"http://example.com\"\n641: - **AND** request with Origin=\"http://evil.com\"\n642: - **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n643: - **THEN** no Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n644: \n645: #### Scenario: Wildcard \"*\" allows any origin\n646: - **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins=[\"*\"]\n647: - **WHEN** any origin is requested\n648: - **THEN** origin is allowed\n649: \n650: #### Scenario: OPTIONS preflight returns 200 without calling next handler\n651: - **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with OPTIONS request\n652: - **WHEN** Wrap processes request\n653: - **THEN** status is 200\n654: - **AND** next handler is not called\n655: \n656: #### Scenario: No Origin header results in no CORS headers\n657: - **GIVEN** a request without Origin header\n658: - **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n659: - **THEN** no CORS headers added\n660: \n661: ---\n662: \n663: ## REQ-014: Logging Middleware\n664: \n665: ### Description\n666: LoggingMiddleware logs request details including method, path, status code, and duration.\n667: \n668: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n669: \n670: #### Scenario: Request is logged with details\n671: - **GIVEN** a LoggingMiddleware with Logger\n672: - **WHEN** request is processed\n673: - **THEN** logger.Info is called with \"request\"\n674: - **AND** args include method, path, status, duration\n675: \n676: #### Scenario: Status code is captured from response\n677: - **GIVEN** a handler that writes specific status code\n678: - **WHEN** LoggingMiddleware wraps handler\n679: - **THEN** logged status matches handler's written status\n680: \n681: ---\n682: \n683: ## REQ-015: Recovery Middleware\n684: \n685: ### Description\n686: RecoveryMiddleware catches panics in handlers and returns HTTP 500 with error logging.\n687: \n688: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n689: \n690: #### Scenario: Panic is caught and 500 returned\n691: - **GIVEN** a RecoveryMiddleware and a handler that panics\n692: - **WHEN** panic occurs during request\n693: - **THEN** HTTP 500 is returned\n694: - **AND** logger.Error is called with panic details\n695: - **AND** \"Internal Server Error\" body is returned\n696: \n697: #### Scenario: Normal request passes through\n698: - **GIVEN** a RecoveryMiddleware and a normal handler\n699: - **WHEN** no panic occurs\n700: - **THEN** handler's response is returned unchanged\n701: \n702: ---\n703: \n704: ## REQ-016: HandlerFunc Adapter\n705: \n706: ### Description\n707: HandlerFuncAdapter wraps function handlers to implement Handler interface with automatic error handling.\n708: \n709: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n710: \n711: #### Scenario: HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls function\n712: - **GIVEN** a HandlerFunc implementation\n713: - **WHEN** ServeHTTP is called\n714: - **THEN** underlying function is invoked\n715: \n716: #### Scenario: HandlerFunc error triggers HandleError\n717: - **GIVEN** a HandlerFunc that returns an error\n718: - **WHEN** ServeHTTP is called\n719: - **THEN** workloadmanager.HandleError is called with the error\n720: \n721: #### Scenario: HandlerFuncAdapter Register adds route\n722: - **GIVEN** a HandlerFuncAdapter with Path=\"/test\"\n723: - **WHEN** Register is called on router\n724: - **THEN** route is registered at \"/test\"\n725: \n726: ---\n727: \n728: ## REQ-017: DeletionReason Constants\n729: \n730: ### Description\n731: DeletionReason constants define reasons for sandbox deletion: IdleTimeout, MaxDurationReached, UserRequest.\n732: \n733: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n734: \n735: #### Scenario: DeletionReason constants have correct values\n736: - **GIVEN** DeletionReason constants\n737: - **WHEN** inspected\n738: - **THEN** DeletionReasonIdleTimeout equals \"IdleTimeout\"\n739: - **AND** DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached equals \"MaxDurationReached\"\n740: - **AND** DeletionReasonUserRequest equals \"UserRequest\"\n741: \n742: ---\n743: \n744: ## REQ-018: SuccessResponse and ErrorResponse\n745: \n746: ### Description\n747: SuccessResponse and ErrorResponse structs define JSON response shapes for HTTP endpoints.\n748: \n749: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n750: \n751: #### Scenario: SuccessResponse contains Data field\n752: - **GIVEN** a SuccessResponse with Data populated\n753: - **WHEN** JSON marshaled\n754: - **THEN** output contains \"data\" key with provided value\n755: \n756: #### Scenario: ErrorResponse contains Code, Message, Details\n757: - **GIVEN** an ErrorResponse with all fields\n758: - **WHEN** JSON marshaled\n759: - **THEN** output contains \"code\", \"message\" keys\n760: - **AND** \"details\" is omitted if empty\n761: \n762: ---\n763: \n764: ## Summary\n765: \n766: | REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n767: |--------|-----------|------------|\n768: | REQ-001 | Error Types / HandleError | 6 |\n769: | REQ-002 | MemoryStore | 14 |\n770: | REQ-003 | SandboxLifecycleManager | 18 |\n771: | REQ-004 | GarbageCollector | 10 |\n772: | REQ-005 | HTTPServer | 6 |\n773: | REQ-006 | K8sClient | 8 |\n774: | REQ-007 | Config | 2 |\n775: | REQ-008 | Constants / GVR | 4 |\n776: | REQ-009 | Router | 2 |\n777: | REQ-010 | Informers | 3 |\n778: | REQ-011 | HealthHandler | 5 |\n779: | REQ-012 | DeletionHandler | 4 |\n780: | REQ-013 | CORS Middleware | 5 |\n781: | REQ-014 | Logging Middleware | 2 |\n782: | REQ-015 | Recovery Middleware | 2 |\n783: | REQ-016 | HandlerFunc Adapter | 3 |\n784: | REQ-017 | DeletionReason | 1 |\n785: | REQ-018 | Response Types | 2 |\n786: \n787: **Total Scenarios:** 77\n788: \n789: ---\n790: \n791: ## Implementation Files\n792: \n793: | Path | Role |\n794: |------|------|\n795: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Error types, interfaces, HandleError |\n796: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | MemoryStore CRUD |\n797: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | SandboxLifecycleManager |\n798: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector |\n799: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTPServer |\n800: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | K8sClient, ClientCache |\n801: | `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` | Config struct |\n802: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants, GVR definitions |\n803: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | Router wrapper |\n804: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | Informers wrapper |\n805: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go` | HandlerFunc, HandlerFuncAdapter |\n806: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | HealthHandler |\n807: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete.go` | DeletionHandler |\n808: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORSMiddleware |\n809: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | LoggingMiddleware |\n810: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | RecoveryMiddleware |\n811: \n812: ---\n813: \n814: ## Test Files (Existing)\n815: \n816: | Path | Coverage |\n817: |------|----------|\n818: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` | Error handling |\n819: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go` | MemoryStore CRUD |\n820: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go` | Lifecycle manager |\n821: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | GC operations |\n822: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` | HTTPServer |\n823: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` | K8sClient |\n824: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` | Constants |\n825: | `pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go` | Config |\n826: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go` | Router |\n827: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` | Informers |\n828: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` | Health endpoints |\n829: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | Deletion handler |\n830: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler_test.go` | HandlerFunc adapter |\n831: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS middleware |\n832: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go` | Logging middleware |\n833: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go` | Recovery middleware |\n834: | `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` | Integration tests |\n835: \n836: ---\n837: \n838: ## Dependencies\n839: \n840: | Dependency | Purpose |\n841: |------------|---------|\n842: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP router |\n843: | `github.com/stretchr/testify` | Testing assertions |\n844: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client |\n845: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | API machinery |\n846: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type |\n847: \n848: ---\n849: \n850: ## Validation Checklist\n851: \n852: - [ ] Error types implement Error() correctly\n853: - [ ] HandleError maps errors to correct HTTP status codes\n854: - [ ] MemoryStore CRUD operations are thread-safe\n855: - [ ] MemoryStore expiration and inactive queries filter correctly\n856: - [ ] SandboxLifecycleManager DeleteSandbox removes from store and Kubernetes\n857: - [ ] SandboxLifecycleManager expiration/idle checks work correctly\n858: - [ ] GarbageCollector runs periodically and deletes expired/inactive\n859: - [ ] HTTPServer Start/Stop lifecycle works correctly\n860: - [ ] K8sClient creates all required clients and informers\n861: - [ ] Config defaults are sensible\n862: - [ ] Constants and GVR definitions match expected values\n863: - [ ] Router wraps chi.Router correctly\n864: - [ ] Informers Start and WaitForCacheSync work\n865: - [ ] HealthHandler /healthz and /readyz endpoints work\n866: - [ ] DeletionHandler handles AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter deletion\n867: - [ ] CORS middleware adds headers for allowed origins\n868: - [ ] Logging middleware captures request details\n869: - [ ] Recovery middleware catches panics\n870: - [ ] HandlerFunc adapter wraps function handlers\n\n(End of file - total 870 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md — AR-038 Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n\n## AR-038 — Go Unit Tests (pkg/workloadmanager)\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n**Base specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Error Types and HTTP Response Handling\n\n### Description","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775900324238,"end":1775900324270}}}}
