{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900552707,"sessionID":"ses_28417dd66ffeB506LTdirue3Y0","part":{"id":"prt_d7bebec4e001pdPkttPWm7V8eq","messageID":"msg_d7be8f4d000175wjBCwaO3xwPO","sessionID":"ses_28417dd66ffeB506LTdirue3Y0","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-655c8fad1562485f890ce70be804ae1f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# delta-spec.md — AR-040 Python SDK/CLI Tests\n\n## AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI Tests\n\n**Module:** sdk-python/tests  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: CodeInterpreterClient Initialization\n\n### Description\nCodeInterpreterClient requires router_url and handles session creation/reuse via ControlPlaneClient.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither router_url argument nor ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient.__init__ is called\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"router_url must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL environment variable is set to \"http://router\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized without explicit router_url\n- **THEN** client.router_url equals \"http://router\"\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL explicit override\n- **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\n- **AND** router_url argument is \"http://explicit-router\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n- **THEN** client.router_url equals \"http://explicit-router\"\n\n#### Scenario: Session created when not provided\n- **GIVEN** session_id argument is not provided\n- **AND** ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns \"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n- **THEN** client._session_id equals \"session-123\"\n- **AND** client._session_created equals True\n\n#### Scenario: Session reused when provided\n- **GIVEN** session_id argument is \"provided-session\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n- **THEN** client._session_id equals \"provided-session\"\n- **AND** client._session_created equals False\n- **AND** no HTTP call to create_session is made\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure cleans up session\n- **GIVEN** session_id was not provided\n- **AND** create_session succeeded returning \"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient initialization raises RuntimeError\n- **THEN** warning is logged\n- **AND** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n- **AND** session_id is set to None\n- **AND** RuntimeError is re-raised\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: CodeInterpreterClient Context Manager\n\n### Description\nCodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol for automatic cleanup.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager enters correctly\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with valid configuration\n- **WHEN** entering context via \"with client as ctx\"\n- **THEN** __enter__ returns self\n- **AND** data plane client is initialized\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager calls stop on exit\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient in context manager\n- **WHEN** context block exits normally\n- **THEN** __exit__ calls stop()\n- **AND** data plane session is closed\n- **AND** control plane session is deleted if _session_created is True\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup on exception\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient in context manager\n- **WHEN** exception occurs inside context block\n- **THEN** __exit__ still calls stop()\n- **AND** exception is propagated after cleanup\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: CodeInterpreterClient Stop Method\n\n### Description\nstop() method closes data plane client and optionally deletes control plane session.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Stop closes data plane and deletes session when created\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with _session_created=True and _session_id=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** stop() is called\n- **THEN** data plane client is closed and set to None\n- **AND** control plane delete_session is called\n- **AND** control plane client is closed\n\n#### Scenario: Stop only closes when session was provided externally\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with _session_created=False and _session_id=\"provided-session\"\n- **WHEN** stop() is called\n- **THEN** data plane client is closed\n- **AND** control plane delete_session is NOT called\n- **AND** control plane client is closed\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: CodeInterpreterClient Operations\n\n### Description\nCodeInterpreterClient delegates operations to CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: execute_command delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n- **WHEN** execute_command(\"ls -la\") is called\n- **THEN** data plane execute_command is called with \"ls -la\"\n- **AND** return value matches data plane response stdout\n\n#### Scenario: run_code python execution path\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with language=\"python\"\n- **WHEN** run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello')\") is called\n- **THEN** timestamped .py file is written via write_file\n- **AND** execute_command is called with \"python3 <filename>\"\n- **AND** stdout from command is returned\n\n#### Scenario: run_code unsupported language\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient\n- **WHEN** run_code(\"javascript\", \"console.log('test')\") is called\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message matching \"Unsupported language\"\n\n#### Scenario: write_file delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n- **WHEN** write_file(\"content\", \"/workspace/test.py\") is called\n- **THEN** data plane write_file is called with same arguments\n\n#### Scenario: upload_file delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n- **AND** valid local file path\n- **WHEN** upload_file(local_path, remote_path) is called\n- **THEN** data plane upload_file is called with same arguments\n\n#### Scenario: download_file delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n- **WHEN** download_file(remote_path, local_path) is called\n- **THEN** data plane download_file is called with same arguments\n\n#### Scenario: list_files delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n- **WHEN** list_files(\"/workspace\") is called\n- **THEN** data plane list_files is called with \"/workspace\"\n- **AND** return value matches data plane response\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: CodeInterpreterClient Verbose Mode\n\n### Description\nVerbose flag controls logger level for debugging.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: verbose=False sets INFO level\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with verbose=False\n- **WHEN** client is initialized\n- **THEN** logger level equals logging.INFO\n\n#### Scenario: verbose=True sets DEBUG level\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with verbose=True\n- **WHEN** client is initialized\n- **THEN** logger level equals logging.DEBUG\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: ControlPlaneClient Initialization\n\n### Description\nControlPlaneClient manages HTTP session for Workload Manager API calls with connection pooling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout values\n- **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient without custom timeout\n- **WHEN** initialized\n- **THEN** timeout equals 120\n- **AND** connect_timeout equals 5.0\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout values\n- **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0\n- **WHEN** initialized\n- **THEN** timeout equals 60\n- **AND** connect_timeout equals 3.0\n\n#### Scenario: Session created with headers\n- **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient\n- **WHEN** initialized\n- **THEN** requests.Session is created\n- **AND** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n\n#### Scenario: URL from explicit argument\n- **GIVEN** workload_manager_url=\"http://explicit-url\"\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** base_url equals \"http://explicit-url\"\n\n#### Scenario: URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable set to \"http://env-url\"\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized without argument\n- **THEN** base_url equals \"http://env-url\"\n\n#### Scenario: URL required raises error\n- **GIVEN** no workload_manager_url argument and no WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"workload_manager_url must be provided\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: ControlPlaneClient Auth Token Resolution\n\n### Description\nAuthorization token is resolved from explicit argument or service account token file.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from explicit argument\n- **GIVEN** auth_token=\"explicit-token\"\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** session Authorization header equals \"Bearer explicit-token\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from file\n- **GIVEN** read_token_from_file returns \"file-token\"\n- **AND** no explicit auth_token\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** session Authorization header equals \"Bearer file-token\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token empty\n- **GIVEN** read_token_from_file returns \"\"\n- **AND** no explicit auth_token\n- **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** Authorization header is NOT set in session\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: ControlPlaneClient Create Session\n\n### Description\ncreate_session POSTs to Workload Manager and returns session ID.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Create session success\n- **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with base_url=\"http://wm\"\n- **AND** response contains {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n- **WHEN** create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=3600) is called\n- **THEN** POST request to \"http://wm/v1/code-interpreter\" is made\n- **AND** JSON body contains name, namespace, ttl\n- **AND** return value equals \"session-123\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing sessionId\n- **GIVEN** response JSON does not contain \"sessionId\"\n- **WHEN** create_session is called\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"sessionId not found\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with metadata\n- **GIVEN** metadata={\"key\": \"value\"}\n- **WHEN** create_session is called with metadata\n- **THEN** JSON body includes metadata field\n\n#### Scenario: Create session metadata null\n- **GIVEN** no metadata provided\n- **WHEN** create_session is called\n- **THEN** JSON body includes metadata as null\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: ControlPlaneClient Delete Session\n\n### Description\ndelete_session handles DELETE request with special 404 handling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** DELETE request succeeds with 200\n- **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n- **THEN** True is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 returns True\n- **GIVEN** DELETE request returns 404 HTTPError\n- **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n- **THEN** True is returned (treated as success)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure returns False\n- **GIVEN** DELETE request returns 500 HTTPError\n- **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n- **THEN** False is returned\n- **AND** error is logged\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session RequestException returns False\n- **GIVEN** requests.RequestException is raised\n- **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n- **THEN** False is returned\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: ControlPlaneClient Close\n\n### Description\nclose() method closes the HTTP session.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Close session\n- **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with active session\n- **WHEN** close() is called\n- **THEN** session.close() is called\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Initialization\n\n### Description\nCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient requires session_id and base_url/router_url combination.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Init with session_id\n- **GIVEN** session_id=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** client.session_id equals \"session-123\"\n\n#### Scenario: Init with base_url\n- **GIVEN** base_url=\"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test/invocations/\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** client.base_url equals the provided base_url\n\n#### Scenario: Init missing params raises error\n- **GIVEN** neither base_url nor router_url provided\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Either base_url or router_url\"\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL constructed from router_url\n- **GIVEN** router_url=\"http://router.example.com\", namespace=\"production\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\"\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** base_url equals \"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/production/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Session Header\n\n### Description\nSession header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all requests.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Session header lowercase\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** client is initialized\n- **THEN** session headers contain \"x-agentcube-session-id\" (lowercase)\n- **AND** header value equals \"session-123\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Execute Command\n\n### Description\nexecute_command POSTs JSON to api/execute endpoint with timeout handling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command success\n- **GIVEN** response contains {\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"}\n- **WHEN** execute_command(\"python3 script.py\") is called\n- **THEN** POST to \"api/execute\" endpoint is made\n- **AND** return value equals \"output\"\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command JSON body\n- **GIVEN** timeout=30\n- **WHEN** execute_command(\"python3 script.py\", timeout=30) is called\n- **THEN** JSON body contains {\"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"], \"timeout\": \"30s\"}\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n- **GIVEN** timeout=30 for command\n- **WHEN** execute_command is called\n- **THEN** read timeout equals 32.0 (timeout + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command non-zero exit raises error\n- **GIVEN** response contains {\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error msg\"}\n- **WHEN** execute_command(\"cmd\") is called\n- **THEN** CommandExecutionError is raised\n- **AND** error.exit_code equals 1\n- **AND** error.stderr equals \"error msg\"\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command list input\n- **GIVEN** command passed as list [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n- **WHEN** execute_command is called\n- **THEN** JSON body command equals [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command default timeout\n- **GIVEN** client with timeout=120\n- **WHEN** execute_command(\"ls\") is called without timeout argument\n- **THEN** JSON body timeout equals \"120s\"\n- **AND** read timeout equals 122.0\n\n---\n\n## REQ-014: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Write File\n\n### Description\nwrite_file POSTs JSON with base64-encoded content to api/files.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Write file base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** content=\"hello world\"\n- **WHEN** write_file(\"hello world\", \"/workspace/test.py\") is called\n- **THEN** JSON body content equals base64-encoded \"hello world\"\n\n#### Scenario: Write file mode\n- **GIVEN** write_file called\n- **WHEN** request is made\n- **THEN** JSON body mode equals \"0644\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-015: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Upload File\n\n### Description\nupload_file POSTs multipart form data with session header.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file multipart\n- **GIVEN** local file exists with content\n- **WHEN** upload_file(local_path, \"/workspace/test.txt\") is called\n- **THEN** multipart POST to \"api/files\" is made\n- **AND** files parameter contains the file\n- **AND** data parameter contains path\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file session header\n- **GIVEN** session_id=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** upload_file is called\n- **THEN** request headers contain x-agentcube-session-id=\"session-123\"\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file not found\n- **GIVEN** local file does not exist\n- **WHEN** upload_file is called\n- **THEN** FileNotFoundError is raised\n\n---\n\n## REQ-016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Download File\n\n### Description\ndownload_file streams response and writes to local file.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Download file stream\n- **GIVEN** remote file exists\n- **WHEN** download_file(\"/workspace/source.txt\", local_path) is called\n- **THEN** GET request with stream=True is made\n- **AND** file content is written to local_path\n\n#### Scenario: Download file creates parent directory\n- **GIVEN** local_path in nonexistent subdirectory\n- **WHEN** download_file is called\n- **THEN** parent directory is created\n- **AND** file is written successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Download file removes leading slash\n- **GIVEN** remote_path=\"/workspace/source.txt\"\n- **WHEN** download_file is called\n- **THEN** request URL contains \"source.txt\" (leading slash removed)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-017: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient List Files\n\n### Description\nlist_files GETs api/files with path query parameter.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: List files with path\n- **GIVEN** response contains {\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n- **WHEN** list_files(\"/workspace\") is called\n- **THEN** GET to \"api/files\" with params path=\"/workspace\"\n- **AND** return value equals {\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n\n#### Scenario: List files default path\n- **GIVEN** no path argument\n- **WHEN** list_files() is called\n- **THEN** params path equals \".\" (default)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-018: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Close\n\n### Description\nclose() method closes the HTTP session.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Close session\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with active session\n- **WHEN** close() is called\n- **THEN** session.close() is called\n\n---\n\n## REQ-019: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\n### Description\nAgentRuntimeClient requires router_url and manages session bootstrap/reuse.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Init all parameters\n- **GIVEN** agent_name=\"test-agent\", namespace=\"test-ns\", router_url=\"http://router\", verbose=True, session_id=\"test-session\", timeout=60, connect_timeout=10.0\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n- **THEN** all fields match provided values\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** no router_url argument and no ROUTER_URL environment variable\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL=\"http://router-env.example.com\"\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized without router_url\n- **THEN** router_url equals \"http://router-env.example.com\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-020: AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap\n\n### Description\nSession ID is bootstrapped from Router GET endpoint when not provided.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Session bootstrap from GET\n- **GIVEN** GET to invocations endpoint returns header x-agentcube-session-id=\"bootstrapped-session\"\n- **AND** no session_id argument provided\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n- **THEN** session_id equals \"bootstrapped-session\"\n\n#### Scenario: Session reuse when provided\n- **GIVEN** session_id=\"provided-session\"\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n- **THEN** session_id equals \"provided-session\"\n- **AND** no GET request is made\n\n---\n\n## REQ-021: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n\n### Description\nAgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Context enter returns self\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient\n- **WHEN** entering context\n- **THEN** __enter__ returns self\n\n#### Scenario: Context exit calls close\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient in context\n- **WHEN** context block exits\n- **THEN** close() is called\n\n#### Scenario: Context exit on exception calls close\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient in context\n- **WHEN** exception occurs in context block\n- **THEN** close() is still called\n- **AND** exception is propagated\n\n---\n\n## REQ-022: AgentRuntimeClient Invoke\n\n### Description\ninvoke POSTs JSON payload to Agent Runtime endpoint.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke delegates to data plane\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\n- **AND** data plane returns {\"result\": \"success\"}\n- **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n- **THEN** result equals {\"result\": \"success\"}\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session raises error\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=None\n- **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout passthrough\n- **GIVEN** timeout=30 argument\n- **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=30) is called\n- **THEN** data plane invoke receives timeout=30\n\n---\n\n## REQ-023: AgentRuntimeClient Close\n\n### Description\nclose() method closes the data plane client.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Close calls data plane close\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with data plane client\n- **WHEN** close() is called\n- **THEN** data plane close() is called\n\n---\n\n## REQ-024: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Initialization\n\n### Description\nAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient manages HTTP session for Agent Runtime invocations.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout values\n- **GIVEN** no custom timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** timeout equals 120\n- **AND** connect_timeout equals 5.0\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout values\n- **GIVEN** timeout=60, connect_timeout=10.0\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** timeout equals 60\n- **AND** connect_timeout equals 10.0\n\n#### Scenario: Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient class\n- **WHEN** SESSION_HEADER is checked\n- **THEN** value equals \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** router_url=\"http://router.example.com\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n- **THEN** base_url equals \"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-025: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Connection Pooling\n\n### Description\nHTTP session uses HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Connection pooling adapters\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n- **WHEN** session adapters are checked\n- **THEN** HTTPAdapter is mounted for http:// and https://\n\n---\n\n## REQ-026: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap Session ID\n\n### Description\nbootstrap_session_id GETs invocation endpoint to obtain session header.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap success\n- **GIVEN** GET returns header x-agentcube-session-id=\"test-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** bootstrap_session_id() is called\n- **THEN** return value equals \"test-session-123\"\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap missing header raises error\n- **GIVEN** GET response has no x-agentcube-session-id header\n- **WHEN** bootstrap_session_id() is called\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-027: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke\n\n### Description\ninvoke POSTs JSON payload with session header.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with session\n- **GIVEN** session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** invoke(\"test-session-123\", {\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n- **THEN** POST to base_url is made\n- **AND** response object is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke headers correct\n- **GIVEN** session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** invoke is called\n- **THEN** request headers contain x-agentcube-session-id=\"test-session-123\"\n- **AND** request headers contain Content-Type=\"application/json\"\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n- **GIVEN** timeout=30 argument\n- **WHEN** invoke is called with timeout=30\n- **THEN** read timeout uses provided value\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout default\n- **GIVEN** no timeout argument\n- **WHEN** invoke is called\n- **THEN** read timeout equals self.timeout (default 120)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-028: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Close\n\n### Description\nclose() method closes the HTTP session.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Close session\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with active session\n- **WHEN** close() is called\n- **THEN** session is closed\n\n---\n\n## REQ-029: Exception Hierarchy\n\n### Description\nAgentCube SDK defines exception hierarchy for error handling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCubeError is Exception\n- **GIVEN** AgentCubeError class\n- **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n- **THEN** issubclass(AgentCubeError, Exception) equals True\n\n#### Scenario: CommandExecutionError is AgentCubeError\n- **GIVEN** CommandExecutionError class\n- **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n- **THEN** issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError is AgentCubeError\n- **GIVEN** SessionError class\n- **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n- **THEN** issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError is AgentCubeError\n- **GIVEN** DataPlaneError class\n- **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n- **THEN** issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n\n---\n\n## REQ-030: CommandExecutionError\n\n### Description\nCommandExecutionError captures command failure details.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all params\n- **GIVEN** exit_code=2, stderr=\"failed\", command=\"ls -la\"\n- **WHEN** CommandExecutionError is created\n- **THEN** error.exit_code equals 2\n- **AND** error.stderr equals \"failed\"\n- **AND** error.command equals \"ls -la\"\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor default command\n- **GIVEN** exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\" (no command)\n- **WHEN** CommandExecutionError is created\n- **THEN** error.command equals None\n\n#### Scenario: Message format\n- **GIVEN** exit_code=2, stderr=\"failed output\"\n- **WHEN** str(error) is called\n- **THEN** equals \"Command failed (exit 2): failed output\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-031: SessionError and DataPlaneError\n\n### Description\nSessionError and DataPlaneError are placeholder exception types.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError docstring\n- **GIVEN** SessionError class\n- **WHEN** docstring is checked\n- **THEN** contains \"session\"\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError inherits from AgentCubeError\n- **GIVEN** SessionError instance\n- **WHEN** isinstance check is performed\n- **THEN** isinstance(error, AgentCubeError) equals True\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError docstring\n- **GIVEN** DataPlaneError class\n- **WHEN** docstring is checked\n- **THEN** contains \"data plane\"\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError inherits from AgentCubeError\n- **GIVEN** DataPlaneError instance\n- **WHEN** isinstance check is performed\n- **THEN** isinstance(error, AgentCubeError) equals True\n\n---\n\n## REQ-032: Package Exports\n\n### Description\nPublic package surface defines what users can import.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n- **GIVEN** from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n- **WHEN** import succeeds\n- **THEN** CodeInterpreterClient is available\n\n#### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n- **GIVEN** from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n- **WHEN** import succeeds\n- **THEN** AgentRuntimeClient is available\n\n#### Scenario: Root __all__ contains exactly two names\n- **GIVEN** agentcube.__all__\n- **WHEN** checked\n- **THEN** contains \"CodeInterpreterClient\" and \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n- **AND** length equals 2\n\n#### Scenario: Clients package exports ControlPlaneClient\n- **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient\n- **WHEN** import succeeds\n- **THEN** ControlPlaneClient is available\n\n#### Scenario: Clients package exports CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n- **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n- **WHEN** import succeeds\n- **THEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is available\n\n#### Scenario: Clients package exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n- **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n- **WHEN** import succeeds\n- **THEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is available\n\n#### Scenario: Clients __all__ contains exactly three names\n- **GIVEN** agentcube.clients.__all__\n- **WHEN** checked\n- **THEN** contains ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n- **AND** length equals 3\n\n---\n\n## REQ-033: Utils - create_session\n\n### Description\ncreate_session creates requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Returns requests.Session\n- **GIVEN** create_session() called\n- **WHEN** result is checked\n- **THEN** isinstance(result, requests.Session) equals True\n\n#### Scenario: Has adapters mounted\n- **GIVEN** session from create_session()\n- **WHEN** adapters are checked\n- **THEN** \"http://\" in session.adapters\n- **AND** \"https://\" in session.adapters\n\n#### Scenario: Custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** pool_connections=5, pool_maxsize=5\n- **WHEN** create_session(5, 5) is called\n- **THEN** returns valid requests.Session\n\n---\n\n## REQ-034: Utils - read_token_from_file\n\n### Description\nread_token_from_file reads and strips token from file.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Read token success\n- **GIVEN** file containing \"my-secret-token\\n\"\n- **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n- **THEN** returns \"my-secret-token\" (stripped)\n\n#### Scenario: Read token file not found\n- **GIVEN** nonexistent file path\n- **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n- **THEN** returns \"\"\n\n#### Scenario: Read token strip whitespace\n- **GIVEN** file containing \"  token-with-spaces  \\n\"\n- **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n- **THEN** returns \"token-with-spaces\"\n\n#### Scenario: Read token multiline preserves content\n- **GIVEN** file containing \"token-line1\\ntoken-line2\\n\"\n- **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n- **THEN** returns \"token-line1\\ntoken-line2\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-035: Utils - get_logger\n\n### Description\nget_logger creates named logger with configurable level.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Returns Logger\n- **GIVEN** get_logger(\"test_logger\") called\n- **WHEN** result is checked\n- **THEN** isinstance(result, logging.Logger) equals True\n- **AND** logger.name equals \"test_logger\"\n\n#### Scenario: Default level INFO\n- **GIVEN** get_logger without level argument\n- **WHEN** logger is created\n- **THEN** level equals logging.INFO\n\n#### Scenario: Custom level int\n- **GIVEN** level=logging.DEBUG\n- **WHEN** get_logger is called\n- **THEN** level equals logging.DEBUG\n\n#### Scenario: Custom level str\n- **GIVEN** level=\"DEBUG\"\n- **WHEN** get_logger is called\n- **THEN** level equals logging.DEBUG\n\n---\n\n## REQ-036: AgentRuntime Integration - Full Lifecycle\n\n### Description\nIntegration tests verify complete session lifecycle.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Full session lifecycle\n- **GIVEN** Router GET returns session header\n- **AND** Router POST returns success\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient used as context manager\n- **THEN** session is bootstrapped\n- **AND** invoke returns correct result\n- **AND** cleanup happens on exit\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke workflow with payload\n- **GIVEN** valid AgentRuntimeClient\n- **WHEN** invoke({\"action\": \"process\", \"data\": \"input\"}) is called\n- **THEN** response payload is returned correctly\n\n#### Scenario: Session reuse across multiple invokes\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session\n- **WHEN** multiple invoke calls are made\n- **THEN** session_id remains constant\n- **AND** all invokes succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap failure handling\n- **GIVEN** Router GET returns no session header\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n- **THEN** ValueError is raised with correct message\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke failure handling\n- **GIVEN** Router POST returns 500\n- **WHEN** invoke is called\n- **THEN** HTTPError is raised\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n|--------|-----------|------------|\n| REQ-001 | CodeInterpreterClient Init | 6 |\n| REQ-002 | CodeInterpreterClient Context Manager | 3 |\n| REQ-003 | CodeInterpreterClient Stop | 2 |\n| REQ-004 | CodeInterpreterClient Operations | 7 |\n| REQ-005 | CodeInterpreterClient Verbose | 2 |\n| REQ-006 | ControlPlaneClient Init | 6 |\n| REQ-007 | ControlPlaneClient Auth Token | 3 |\n| REQ-008 | ControlPlaneClient Create Session | 4 |\n| REQ-009 | ControlPlaneClient Delete Session | 4 |\n| REQ-010 | ControlPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n| REQ-011 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Init | 4 |\n| REQ-012 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Session Header | 1 |\n| REQ-013 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Execute Command | 6 |\n| REQ-014 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Write File | 2 |\n| REQ-015 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Upload File | 3 |\n| REQ-016 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Download File | 3 |\n| REQ-017 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient List Files | 2 |\n| REQ-018 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n| REQ-019 | AgentRuntimeClient Init | 3 |\n| REQ-020 | AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap | 2 |\n| REQ-021 | AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager | 3 |\n| REQ-022 | AgentRuntimeClient Invoke | 3 |\n| REQ-023 | AgentRuntimeClient Close | 1 |\n| REQ-024 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Init | 4 |\n| REQ-025 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Pooling | 1 |\n| REQ-026 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap | 2 |\n| REQ-027 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke | 4 |\n| REQ-028 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n| REQ-029 | Exception Hierarchy | 4 |\n| REQ-030 | CommandExecutionError | 3 |\n| REQ-031 | SessionError/DataPlaneError | 4 |\n| REQ-032 | Package Exports | 7 |\n| REQ-033 | Utils create_session | 3 |\n| REQ-034 | Utils read_token_from_file | 4 |\n| REQ-035 | Utils get_logger | 4 |\n| REQ-036 | AgentRuntime Integration | 5 |\n\n**Total Scenarios:** 104\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Root package exports |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | CodeInterpreterClient |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | AgentRuntimeClient |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Clients package exports |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` | create_session |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py` | read_token_from_file |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py` | get_logger |\n\n---\n\n## Test Files (Existing)\n\n| Path | Coverage |\n|------|----------|\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient HTTP |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | AgentRuntimeClient |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_exports.py` | Package exports |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py` | Utility functions |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_integration.py` | Integration tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `pytest` | Test framework |\n| `responses` | HTTP mocking |\n| `requests` | HTTP client |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterClient router_url required and resolution\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterClient session creation and reuse\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterClient context manager cleanup\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterClient operation delegation\n- [ ] ControlPlaneClient HTTP session management\n- [ ] ControlPlaneClient auth token resolution\n- [ ] ControlPlaneClient create/delete session\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header (lowercase)\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command timeout handling\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeClient session bootstrap\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeClient invoke delegation\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL and headers\n- [ ] Exception hierarchy correct inheritance\n- [ ] Package exports match __all__\n- [ ] Utility functions work correctly\n- [ ] Integration tests cover full lifecycle"},"output":"Wrote file successfully."